Here’s what you can expect:

So proud of my team today! Our brand transformation agency Motto® @wearemotto has won the Certified Most Loved Workplace certificate. 

When @ashleigh_hansberger and I fired up Motto, we were determined to establish a #culture that anyone would love to be part of.

Like all companies trying to do anything innovative, we’ve not done it perfectly or without flaws. However, we have gotten some really important things right. 

Motto was recently evaluated using the Love of Workplace Index™ Pulse Survey, a comprehensive tool for measuring employees’ sentiments toward their workplace. The survey analyzed aspects like collaboration, career growth, respect at all levels, and alignment of employee and employer values.

What makes Motto® a Certified Most Loved Workplace®, and how can you become one too? 

→️ A positive vision of the future.
→️ Respect for the team (even when disagreeing).
→️ Support in achieving professional and personal dreams.
→️ Values alignment to enhance engagement and motivation.
→️ A CEO leadership style that inspires big thinking.
→️ Unique benefits that make everyone feel valued and appreciated.
→️ Unwavering commitment to systemic collaboration.
→️ A “we before me” mindset and open communication.
→️ Promoting cross-functional projects towards creativity, innovation, and team unity.
→️ Investing in professional development opportunities like mentorship and coaching.
→️ Supporting employees in reaching their professional and personal goals.

These are just some unique benefits that set Motto apart as a Certified Most Loved Workplace®. 

#innovation #leadership #brand #career #team
You don’t miss the water, until the well runs dry.

Seek commitment, not consensus. Aligning leaders in a workshop or visioning sessions is never linear. It involves many big ideas, voices, perspectives, and opinions.

It’s easy to expect a smooth process towards consensus, but innovation requires opposing ideas and audacious thinking.

To aim for commitment, at Motto® we must first encourage the sharing of ideas in a safe, open space. This enables leaders to discourse, rather than feel part of an agreeing culture that only allows room for ‘yes’ people.

Find a thread that runs through all the insights, and rally everyone to commit to a single, crystallized idea.

Give all perspectives a seat at the table, then ask for commitment, even amongst those that disagree. You will find commitment to the path forward easier than consensus across the board.

It's not every day you and your fedora land on the cover of a magazine!

I'm honored to have made the cover of SWAGGER magazine's SELF-MADE edition. Past features include Ryan Reynolds, Jason Oppenheimer, and Michael B. Jordon. To be recognized as a branding icon and visionary, I'm pretty blown away and very humbled.

SWAGGER is a high-profile go-to lifestyle magazine and they also feature inspiring journeys of people who have built incredible things from nothing.

@ashleigh_hansberger and I built @wearemotto surrounded by doubt. Every dollar we made went right back into the business. Every stripe earned and fought for.

I can be visionary because I have an incredible co-conspirator who is a genius strategic mastermind and an incredible team who allows me to chase those ideas. 

My favorite part of the article is:

🏴 The five important lessons I’ve learned which can be applied to entrepreneurship at any part of the game:

✔️ Success goes to those who can handle the pressure.
✔️ Ask yourself whether you are playing Little League or Major League Baseball.
✔️ Leadership and loneliness are like peanut butter and jelly. Don’t expect people to understand. Not your team, not your family.
✔️ Don’t be the best-kept secret: You are your biggest cheerleader.
✔️ Seek commitment, not compliance. You want people to follow you because they want to, not because they have to.

Special shoutout to Nathan Holloway for creating such a superb design piece.

“What if you could take the parts of yourself that other people criticize - traits they call defiant, dangerous, and different - and turn them into your selling points?” 

That’s the question @ashleigh_hansberger and I set out to answer in our bestseller Rare Breed: A Guide to Success for the Defiant, Dangerous, and Different. 

Awhile back @robmeyerson interviewed me about my journey as the CEO of @wearemotto and how Rare Breed thinking plays a role. 

Here’s a snippet of that interview. If you’ve ever felt like you didn’t belong, this soundbite will resonate with you deeply. 

The idea is simple yet powerful: being defiant, dangerous, and different is a gift, and by embracing these qualities, you unlock the potential to succeed authentically, not despite societal perceptions, but by staying true to who you are.

In a world that often prizes conformity and well-trodden paths, I hope this quote serves as a clarion call for leaders and visionaries. 

It reminds us that at the heart of every great leap forward lies a rebellious spirit - a willingness to see beyond the status quo and imagine what could be.

True visionaries are those who dare to think differently. 

They are the architects of change, the ones who challenge conventional wisdom and push boundaries. Their journey is not one of comfort but of constant questioning and relentless pursuit of what could be, rather than what is.

The very act of vision is, indeed, an act of rebellion. It's a rebellion against mediocrity, against the mundane, and against the limits of what is. It's a call to arms for every leader, every dreamer, every innovator.
